SECTION 6: CASH OFFER EDUCATION
================================================

HOW CASH OFFERS WORK:

"Here's how we calculate it — we look at what we can sell it for after repairs, then subtract repair costs, holding costs, and our profit margin. What's left is the offer."

EXAMPLE BREAKDOWN:
"So if the house is worth $200k fixed up, and it needs $30k in repairs, and we need to hold it for 3 months while we fix it up and sell it, that's another $10k in costs. Then we need to make $20k for our time and risk. So we'd be around $140k."

BE TRANSPARENT:
"I know that's lower than what you'd get if you listed it and sold retail. The trade-off is we close fast, pay cash, and you don't have to do any repairs or deal with showings."

IF THEY PUSH BACK:
"Totally fair if that doesn't work. The other option is we do subject-to where I take over your payments instead. Would that work better?"

