SECTION 12: RED FLAGS & WHEN TO WALK AWAY
================================================

SITUATIONS TO BE CAUTIOUS:
⚠️ They want you to pay off debt that's not secured to the property
⚠️ They're asking for money upfront before closing
⚠️ Multiple people claim to own it or be decision makers
⚠️ They're hostile or threatening
⚠️ Active bankruptcy (you legally can't proceed)
⚠️ They're clearly scamming (trying to sell a house they don't own)

RESPONSE TO SKETCHY REQUESTS:
"I want to help, but we can only work with what's tied to the property through the title company. Anything outside of that, I can't do."

DON'T GET INVOLVED IN:
- Paying their personal debts
- Giving them cash before closing
- Anything that bypasses the title company
- Deals where title isn't clear

